This is about Enron movie trading business where we are a market maker for=20
trading future of a movie's gross box office receipt. Rich sent to many=20
people a writing explaining his movie trading idea and asked us to provide=20
some feedback.

I think the idea (see below) might be applicable to other parts of Enron. We=
=20
can call it "Dynamic bid-ask price process".
In fact, we can set that the bidding period is closed when no new bid is=20
submitted to the system within a specified amount of time. The final=20
(clearing) bid and ask prices are just the last "tentative" price shown to=20
the public before the bidding period ends. (So the customers can see the=20
final price before the market close and can revise their bids if they wish.)

I think this method is suitable for illiquid products to be traded via=20
EnronOnline.com.
-Chonawee


